. When we make significant changes, we will:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>• Update the \"Last Updated\" Date: Clear indication of when changes were made</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>• Notify Users: Email notification for significant changes</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>• Post Updated Version: Make the new policy available on our website</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>• Continued Use: Continued use indicates acceptance of changes</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>13. CONTACT US</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Privacy Team Contact</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Email: privacy@breachfix.com</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Response within 48 hours</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mailing Address:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BREACHFIX Privacy Team</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>123 Privacy Street</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Toronto, ON M5H 2N2</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Canada</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>General Support</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Data Protection Officer: dpo@breachfix.com</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For GDPR-related inquiries</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Customer Support: support@breachfix.com</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>General account assistance</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Questions or Concerns?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please don\'t hesitate to contact us. We\'re committed to addressing your privacy concerns promptly and transparently.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BREACHFIX</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Your privacy is our priority. Thank you for trusting BREACHFIX with your data.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Last updated: January 1, 2025</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Privacy policy','','inherit','closed','closed','','15-revision-v1','','','2025-09-30 21:48:13','2025-09-30 21:48:13','',15,'http://breachfix-university.local/?p=18',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (19,1,'2025-09-30 21:54:10','2025-09-30 21:54:10','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>PRIVACY POLICY</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Effective Date: January 1, 2025</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Last Updated: January 1, 2025</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BREACHFIX (\"we,\" \"our,\" or \"us\") values your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect the data you share with us when you use our website, applications, and services (collectively, the \"Services\").</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>OVERVIEW</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At BREACHFIX, we believe in transparency about how we handle your personal information. This policy covers all aspects of data collection, usage, and protection across our platform. We are committed to keeping your data secure through industry-standard encryption, maintaining transparent and clear data practices, and giving you control to manage your own data.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>INFORMATION WE COLLECT</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We collect several types of information from and about users of our Services. Personal Information includes your name and email address, account login details, billing address and payment details, as well as profile information and preferences. Content Information encompasses any media and text you upload or submit, comments and interactions on our platform, and your saved favorites and playlists. Usage Information includes your IP address and browser type, device information and access times, pages viewed and features used, as well as performance and error logs. We also collect Cookies and Tracking Data, which includes session cookies for authentication, analytics cookies for performance insights, preference cookies for personalization, and marketing cookies which are only used with your consent.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We use your information for several important purposes. For Service Delivery, we use your data to provide and maintain our Services, process transactions and subscriptions, handle pay-per-view payments, and deliver content and features to you. For Improvement and Personalization, we enhance and expand BREACHFIX features, personalize your experience, recommend relevant content, and optimize platform performance. For Communication purposes, we send service updates and notifications, provide customer support, share information about new features and promotions, and send important security alerts. For Security and Compliance, we use your information to protect against fraud and abuse, monitor for security risks, comply with legal obligations, and enforce our terms of service.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>PAYMENT AND CREDIT CARD INFORMATION</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BREACHFIX takes the security of your payment information very seriously. We do not store your full credit card details on our servers. All payments are processed through secure, PCI-DSS compliant third-party providers such as Stripe. We do not store full credit card numbers, CVV codes, expiration dates, or billing addresses. What we do store includes transaction IDs, payment status, subscription details, and billing history. This approach ensures that your sensitive payment information is handled with the highest level of security and in compliance with industry standards.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>HOW WE SHARE INFORMATION</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BREACHFIX does not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties. We only share data in limited circumstances. We work with trusted service providers who help us operate our platform, including cloud hosting and infrastructure providers, payment processing services, analytics and performance monitoring tools, customer support platforms, and email and notification services. These service providers are contractually obligated to protect your data and use it only for the purposes we specify. We may also share data when required by law, such as to comply with legal obligations, in response to court orders, to protect our rights and property, to prevent fraud or abuse, or in case of business transfers such as mergers or acquisitions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>COOKIES AND TRACKING</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We use various types of cookies and tracking technologies to provide and improve our Services. Essential Cookies are required for basic website functionality and cannot be disabled. These cookies keep you signed in to your account, remember your preferences and settings, maintain your session security, and enable core platform features. Analytics Cookies help us understand how you use our platform by analyzing traffic and site performance, identifying popular content and features, monitoring for errors and issues, and helping us improve the overall user experience. You can disable cookies in your browser settings, but please note that this may limit some functionality of our Services. Essential cookies cannot be disabled as they are required for basic operation. To manage cookies, you can adjust your browser settings. In Chrome, go to Settings, then Privacy and security, then Cookies. In Firefox, navigate to Settings, then Privacy &amp; Security, then Cookies. In Safari, go to Preferences, then Privacy, then Cookies. In Edge, access Settings, then Cookies and site permissions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>DATA RETENTION</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We retain your personal information only as long as necessary to provide our Services, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. For Active Accounts, we retain account data while your account is active, content until you delete it, usage data for 24 months, and payment records for 7 years as required by law. For Deleted Accounts, we retain personal data for 30 days to allow for account recovery, anonymized analytics for 24 months for statistical purposes, legal compliance data as required by applicable laws, and backup data for 90 days.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>SECURITY</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We implement comprehensive security measures to protect your data. Our security measures include end-to-end encryption for sensitive data, secure servers with restricted access, regular security audits and monitoring, and ongoing staff training on data protection. We adhere to industry security standards including AES-256 encryption, PCI-DSS compliance for all payment processing, HTTPS encryption for all communications, and regular security updates and patches. While we implement industry-standard safeguards to protect your data, it is important to understand that no method of transmission or storage is one hundred percent secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security but we are committed to continuous improvement and maintaining the highest security standards possible.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CHILDREN\'S PRIVACY</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BREACHFIX does not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13 years of age, or the age required by local law in your jurisdiction, whichever is higher. Our Services are not intended for children under 13. If we discover that we have collected personal information from a child under the applicable age limit, we will immediately delete that personal information, disable the account if applicable, notify parents or guardians if their contact information is available, and report to appropriate authorities if required by law. If you believe we may have any information from or about a child under the applicable age, please contact us immediately.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>YOUR RIGHTS</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal data. These rights may include the right to Access, which allows you to request a copy of your personal data; the right to Correction, which allows you to update or correct inaccurate data; the right to Deletion, which allows you to request deletion of your data; the right to Portability, which allows you to export your data in a portable format; the right to Restriction, which allows you to limit how we process your data; and the right to Objection, which allows you to object to certain processing activities. To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information provided in the Contact Us section below. We will respond to your request within 30 days. When making a request, please provide your full name and email address, specify which right you want to exercise, provide a description of the data in question, and be prepared to verify your identity for security purposes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>INTERNATIONAL USERS</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BREACHFIX operates primarily in Canada, but your data may be processed in other countries where our service providers are located. By using our Services, you consent to the transfer of your data outside your country of residence. We ensure adequate protection measures are in place for all international data transfers, including standard contractual clauses, regular compliance audits, and adherence to privacy shield frameworks where applicable. Regardless of your location, you have the same rights with respect to your data, and we comply with local privacy laws, ensure cross-border data protection, and maintain appropriate regulatory oversight.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CHANGES TO THIS POLICY</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technology, legal requirements, or other factors. When we make significant changes, we will update the \"Last Updated\" date at the top of this policy to provide clear indication of when changes were made. We will notify users via email for significant changes, post the updated version on our website to make it readily available, and your continued use of our Services after such changes indicates your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CONTACT US</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please don\'t hesitate to contact us. We\'re committed to addressing your privacy concerns promptly and transparently. You can reach our Privacy Team by email at privacy@breachfix.com, and we will respond within 48 hours. You can also contact us by mail at BREACHFIX Privacy Team, 123 Privacy Street, Toronto, ON M5H 2N2, Canada. For GDPR-related inquiries, you can contact our Data Protection Officer at dpo@breachfix.com. For general account assistance, you can reach our Customer Support at support@breachfix.com.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BREACHFIX - Your privacy is our priority. Thank you for trusting BREACHFIX with your data.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Last updated: January 1, 2025</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Privacy policy','','inherit','closed','closed','','15-revision-v1','','','2025-09-30 21:54:10','2025-09-30 21:54:10','',15,'http://breachfix-university.local/?p=19',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (20,1,'2025-09-30 22:06:24','2025-09-30 22:06:24','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>About Us – Fiction University</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Fiction University is more than a place of study — it is a vision for a renewed world of knowledge.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here, learning is not confined to walls or textbooks, but expands into the heart, mind, and life of each student.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We believe that true education is not only about gaining a career but about transforming lives for the better.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our mission is to awaken curiosity, to stir thought, and to equip people with the tools to think critically and live meaningfully.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At Fiction University, we stand against ignorance by opening doors to understanding.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We seek to replace confusion with clarity, fear with wisdom, and passivity with empowerment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Every subject we teach, every lecture we offer, carries the goal of lifting minds higher than human tradition.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We invite learners not only to master skills but to embrace truth that transcends the ordinary.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our vision is for education that does not stop at information but moves into re-education —</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>a learning that reshapes, rebuilds, and redefines what it means to live with purpose.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We prepare students for the challenges of their careers, yes, but also for the responsibilities of life.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In every classroom, whether physical or digital, we cultivate character, resilience, and vision.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Fiction University believes that knowledge is a gift meant to be shared.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is the foundation of freedom, the antidote to deception, and the path to a brighter future.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We are committed to making education accessible, transformative, and enduring.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Each graduate carries more than a certificate — they carry a renewed mind and a mission.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is Fiction University: a place where minds awaken, lives are rebuilt, and futures are reimagined.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A place where education reaches beyond limits, and truth becomes the greatest teacher of all.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','About Us','','publish','closed','closed','','about-us','','','2025-09-30 22:06:24','2025-09-30 22:06:24','',0,'http://breachfix-university.local/?page_id=20',0,'page','',0);
